11/30/00

  Brenchmark results:

  Input is DiviCom at 5 Mbps video, no audio.  Output set at various rate.

  Baseline is RecodeOneMb and Flush2Mux in C, and all other in assembly.
  RecodeOneMb and Flush2Mux is always C version in the following tests.
  Without rate reduction (27 Mbps output), CPU load is always about 14%.

  Code								4.9   4.5   4.0
  1100	Baseline						 23    47    55
  1101	All in C						 40   *99    *
  1102  C: Encode inter/intra block, A: others			 29    72   ~90
  1103  A: Encode inter/intra block, input, C: others		 30    73   ~90 
  1104  C: mode, A: others					 23    47    55
  1105: C: Mv, getMv, parseMv, A: others			 23    47    55
  1106: C: inPass, startCode, A: others				 23    47    56 

  1110: C: mode,Mv,getMv,parseMv,inPass,startCode, A: others	 23    47    63


  Conclusion:
    Insignificant: mode, Mv, getMv, parseMv, inPass, startCode
    Encode inter/intra contribute to about half of total improvement

  Extended test:
		  8->7   8->6   8->5
  1100		   60    ~74     57
  1110		   63    ~80     57

